#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.3:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Sambodhivagga"
msgstr "1. Awakening"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an9.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Meghiyasutta"
msgstr "3. With Meghiya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā cālikāyaṃ viharati cālikāpabbate."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā meghiyo bhagavato upaṭṭhāko hoti."
msgstr "Now, at that time Venerable Meghiya was the Buddha’s attendant."

msgctxt "an9.3:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā meghiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho āyasmā "
"meghiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Meghiya went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and "
"said to him:"

#. VAR: jantugāmaṃ → jatugāmaṃ (bj-a, s-a) | jattugāmaṃ (mr aṭṭhakathāyampi pāṭhantaraṃ)
msgctxt "an9.3:1.4"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, jantugāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisitun”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, I’d like to enter Jantu village for alms.”"

msgctxt "an9.3:1.5"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, meghiya, kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, Meghiya, go when it’s convenient.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.355"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā meghiyo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"jantugāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then Meghiya robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered "
"Jantu village for alms."

msgctxt "an9.3:2.2"
msgid ""
"Jantugāme piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena kimikāḷāya "
"nadiyā tīraṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"After the meal, on his return from alms-round in Jantu village, he went to "
"the shore of Kimikālā river."

#. VAR: jaṅghāvihāraṃ → jaṅghavihāraṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an9.3:2.3"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho āyasmā meghiyo kimikāḷāya nadiyā tīre jaṅghāvihāraṃ "
"anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno ambavanaṃ pāsādikaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"As he was going for a walk along the shore of the river he saw a lovely and "
"delightful mango grove."

msgctxt "an9.3:2.4"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "It occurred to him:"

msgctxt "an9.3:2.5"
msgid ""
"“pāsādikaṃ vatidaṃ ambavanaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ, alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa "
"padhānatthikassa padhānāya."
msgstr ""
"“Oh, this mango grove is lovely and delightful! It’s truly good enough for "
"meditation for a kinsman who wants to meditate."

msgctxt "an9.3:2.6"
msgid "Sace maṃ bhagavā anujāneyya, āgaccheyyāhaṃ imaṃ ambavanaṃ padhānāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"If the Buddha allows me, I’ll come back to this mango grove to meditate.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā meghiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā "
"meghiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Meghiya went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and told him what had happened. He then said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya jantugāmaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.2"
msgid ""
"Jantugāme piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena kimikāḷāya "
"nadiyā tīraṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.3"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, kimikāḷāya nadiyā tīre jaṅghāvihāraṃ "
"anucaṅkamamāno anuvicaramāno ambavanaṃ pāsādikaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.4"
msgid "Disvāna me etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.5"
msgid "‘pāsādikaṃ vatidaṃ ambavanaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.6"
msgid "Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.7"
msgid "Sace maṃ bhagavā anujāneyya, āgaccheyyāhaṃ imaṃ ambavanaṃ padhānāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:4.8"
msgid "Sace maṃ bhagavā anujāneyya, gaccheyyāhaṃ taṃ ambavanaṃ padhānāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“If the Buddha allows me, I’ll go back to that mango grove to meditate.”"

#. VAR: Ekakamhi → ekakamhā (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: tāva → vata (mr)
#. VAR: āgacchatī”ti → dissatūti (sabbattha, ṭīkāyampi pāṭhantaraṃ) | dissatīti (ṭīkāyaṃ pāṭhantarāni)
msgctxt "an9.3:4.9"
msgid ""
"“Āgamehi tāva, meghiya. Ekakamhi tāva yāva aññopi koci bhikkhu āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "“We’re alone, Meghiya. Wait until another mendicant comes.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:5.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā meghiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time Meghiya said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an9.3:5.2"
msgid ""
"“bhagavato, bhante, natthi kiñci uttari karaṇīyaṃ, natthi katassa paṭicayo."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the Buddha has nothing more to do, and nothing that needs improvement."

msgctxt "an9.3:5.3"
msgid ""
"Mayhaṃ kho pana, bhante, atthi uttari karaṇīyaṃ, atthi katassa paṭicayo."
msgstr "But I have."

msgctxt "an9.3:5.4"
msgid "Sace maṃ bhagavā anujāneyya, gaccheyyāhaṃ taṃ ambavanaṃ padhānāyā”ti."
msgstr "If you allow me, I’ll go back to that mango grove to meditate.”"

msgctxt "an9.3:5.5"
msgid ""
"“Āgamehi tāva, meghiya, ekakamhi tāva yāva aññopi koci bhikkhu āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr "“We’re alone, Meghiya. Wait until another mendicant comes.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.356"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:6.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā meghiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time Meghiya said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an9.3:6.2"
msgid ""
"“bhagavato, bhante, natthi kiñci uttari karaṇīyaṃ, natthi katassa paṭicayo."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the Buddha has nothing more to do, and nothing that needs improvement."

msgctxt "an9.3:6.3"
msgid ""
"Mayhaṃ kho pana, bhante, atthi uttari karaṇīyaṃ, atthi katassa paṭicayo."
msgstr "But I have."

msgctxt "an9.3:6.4"
msgid "Sace maṃ bhagavā anujāneyya, gaccheyyāhaṃ taṃ ambavanaṃ padhānāyā”ti."
msgstr "If you allow me, I’ll go back to that mango grove to meditate.”"

msgctxt "an9.3:6.5"
msgid "“Padhānanti kho, meghiya, vadamānaṃ kinti vadeyyāma."
msgstr "“Meghiya, since you speak of meditation, what can I say?"

msgctxt "an9.3:6.6"
msgid "Yassadāni tvaṃ, meghiya, kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "Please, Meghiya, go when it’s convenient.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā meghiyo uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ "
"katvā yena taṃ ambavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ ambavanaṃ "
"ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then Meghiya got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the "
"Buddha, keeping him on his right. Then he went to that mango grove, and, "
"having plunged deep into it, sat at the root of a certain tree for the day’s "
"meditation."

msgctxt "an9.3:7.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmato meghiyassa tasmiṃ ambavane viharantassa yebhuyyena tayo "
"pāpakā akusalā vitakkā samudācaranti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"But while Meghiya was meditating in that mango grove he was beset mostly by "
"three kinds of bad, unskillful thoughts, namely,"

msgctxt "an9.3:7.3"
msgid "kāmavitakko, byāpādavitakko, vihiṃsāvitakko."
msgstr "sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts."

msgctxt "an9.3:7.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato meghiyassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "an9.3:7.5"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an9.3:7.6"
msgid "Saddhāya ca vatamhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā;"
msgstr "I’ve gone forth from the lay life to homelessness out of faith."

msgctxt "an9.3:7.7"
msgid "atha ca panimehi tīhi pāpakehi akusalehi vitakkehi anvāsattā—"
msgstr ""
"but I’m still harassed by these three kinds of bad, unskillful thoughts:"

msgctxt "an9.3:7.8"
msgid "kāmavitakkena, byāpādavitakkena, vihiṃsāvitakkenā”ti."
msgstr "sensual, malicious, and cruel thoughts.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:8.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā meghiyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā "
"meghiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Meghiya went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and told him what had happened."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.357"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha mayhaṃ, bhante, tasmiṃ ambavane viharantassa yebhuyyena tayo pāpakā "
"akusalā vitakkā samudācaranti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:9.2"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:9.3"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:9.4"
msgid "Saddhāya ca vatamhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:9.5"
msgid "atha ca panimehi tīhi pāpakehi akusalehi vitakkehi anvāsattā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an9.3:9.6"
msgid "kāmavitakkena, byāpādavitakkena, vihiṃsāvitakkenā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:10.1"
msgid ""
"“Aparipakkāya, meghiya, cetovimuttiyā pañca dhammā paripakkāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"“Meghiya, when the heart’s release is not ripe, five things help it ripen."

msgctxt "an9.3:10.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an9.3:10.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, meghiya, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko."
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant has good friends, companions, and associates."

msgctxt "an9.3:10.4"
msgid ""
"Aparipakkāya, meghiya, cetovimuttiyā ayaṃ paṭhamo dhammo paripakkāya "
"saṃvattati. (1)"
msgstr "This is the first thing …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:11.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto "
"viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya "
"sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and "
"has appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an9.3:11.2"
msgid ""
"Aparipakkāya, meghiya, cetovimuttiyā ayaṃ dutiyo dhammo paripakkāya "
"saṃvattati. (2)"
msgstr "This is the second thing …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:12.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, meghiya, yāyaṃ kathā abhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, "
"seyyathidaṃ—appicchakathā santuṭṭhikathā pavivekakathā asaṃsaggakathā "
"vīriyārambhakathā sīlakathā samādhikathā paññākathā vimuttikathā "
"vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā kathāya nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī "
"akasiralābhī."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant gets to take part in talk about self-effacement "
"that helps open the heart, when they want, without trouble or difficulty. "
"That is, talk about fewness of wishes, contentment, seclusion, keeping your "
"distance, arousing energy, ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and the "
"knowledge and vision of freedom."

msgctxt "an9.3:12.2"
msgid ""
"Aparipakkāya, meghiya, cetovimuttiyā ayaṃ tatiyo dhammo paripakkāya "
"saṃvattati. (3)"
msgstr "This is the third thing …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:13.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhu āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo "
"anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant lives with energy roused up for giving up "
"unskillful qualities and gaining skillful qualities. They are strong, firmly "
"applied, not slacking off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an9.3:13.2"
msgid ""
"Aparipakkāya, meghiya, cetovimuttiyā ayaṃ catuttho dhammo paripakkāya "
"saṃvattati. (4)"
msgstr "This is the fourth thing …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhu paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "an9.3:14.2"
msgid ""
"Aparipakkāya, meghiya, cetovimuttiyā ayaṃ pañcamo dhammo paripakkāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"This is the fifth thing that, when the heart’s release is not ripe, helps it "
"ripen."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.358"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:15.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa:"
msgstr "A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to"

msgctxt "an9.3:15.2"
msgid "‘sīlavā bhavissati … pe … samādāya sikkhissati sikkhāpadesu’."
msgstr "be ethical …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:16.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa:"
msgstr "A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to"

msgctxt "an9.3:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘yāyaṃ kathā abhisallekhikā cetovivaraṇasappāyā, seyyathidaṃ—appicchakathā … "
"pe … vimuttiñāṇadassanakathā, evarūpiyā kathāya nikāmalābhī bhavissati "
"akicchalābhī akasiralābhī’."
msgstr "take part in talk about self-effacement that helps open the heart …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:17.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa: ‘āraddhavīriyo viharissati … pe … anikkhittadhuro "
"kusalesu dhammesu’."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to be "
"energetic …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:18.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, meghiya, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa: ‘paññavā bhavissati … pe … sammādukkhakkhayagāminiyā’. "
"(5)"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to be "
"wise …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an9.3:19.1"
msgid ""
"Tena ca pana, meghiya, bhikkhunā imesu pañcasu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya cattāro "
"dhammā uttari bhāvetabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A mendicant grounded on these five things should develop four further things."

msgctxt "an9.3:19.2"
msgid ""
"asubhā bhāvetabbā rāgassa pahānāya, mettā bhāvetabbā byāpādassa pahānāya, "
"ānāpānassati bhāvetabbā vitakkupacchedāya, aniccasaññā bhāvetabbā "
"asmimānasamugghātāya."
msgstr ""
"They should develop the perception of ugliness to give up greed, love to "
"give up hate, mindfulness of breathing to cut off thinking, and perception "
"of impermanence to uproot the conceit ‘I am’."

msgctxt "an9.3:19.3"
msgid "Aniccasaññino, meghiya, anattasaññā saṇṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"When you perceive impermanence, the perception of not-self becomes "
"stabilized."

msgctxt "an9.3:19.4"
msgid ""
"Anattasaññī asmimānasamugghātaṃ pāpuṇāti diṭṭheva dhamme nibbānan”ti. (6–9.)"
msgstr ""
"Perceiving not-self, you uproot the conceit ‘I am’ and attain extinguishment "
"in this very life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.3:19.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
